<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="930" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 892.001/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Tarler</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-10-23"><hi rend="italic">October 23,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>His Majesty the King of Siam died 12.45 this morning. His Royal Highness
                            Crown Prince Vajiravudh has been proclaimed King of Siam. Have sent the
                            message of condolence for the President to the minister for foreign
                            affairs of Siam.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Tarler.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>